speechtext:
Madam Speaker, I think you will find that there is unanimous consent to the following:
That, in relation to Bill C-63, an act to terminate certain corporations and other bodies, the remainder of this sitting day should be allotted to report stage and one sitting day should be allotted to third reading stage of the bill;
That, if necessary, the debate at report stage shall continue tonight beyond the hour of daily adjournment, but no later than 9 a.m. on Thursday, November 26, 1992, until all questions necessary to dispose of the report stage of the said bill are disposed of, provided that no dilatory motion or quorum call shall be deemed receivable during the extended sitting, and that any requested division shall be deferred until 10 a.m., Thursday, November 26, 1992;
That, notwithstanding any Standing Order, on Thursday, November 26, 1992 the House shall proceed with the third reading stage of Bill C-63.
That, if necessary, the debate at the third reading stage shall continue beyond the hour of daily adjournment on Thursday, November 26,1992, but no later than 10 a.m. on Friday, November 27,1992, until all questions necessary to dispose of the third reading stage of the said bill are disposed of, provided that no dilatory motion or quorum calls shall be deemed receivable during the extended sitting, and if a recorded division is requested, it shall be deferred until 6 p.m., Monday, November 30, 1992.
